Paul and Silas began to pray and sing praises to God at night.

00:02:09.600 --> 00:02:14.210
Around midnight, the ground suddenly shook so hard

00:02:14.210 --> 00:02:16.610
that the doors of the jail fell open!

00:02:16.610 --> 00:02:19.050
And the chains fell off the prisoners.

00:02:19.050 --> 00:02:21.050
It was an earthquake!

00:02:21.050 --> 00:02:24.650
The jailer was sure all the prisoners had escaped.

00:02:24.650 --> 00:02:26.650
But just then, Paul shouted.

00:02:26.650 --> 00:02:28.260
"We are all here!"

00:02:28.260 --> 00:02:31.720
“Bring me a light!” the jailer called to a servant.

00:02:31.720 --> 00:02:34.220
He ran to look for himself.

00:02:34.220 --> 00:02:37.360
Not one prisoner had run away!

00:02:37.360 --> 00:02:40.970
The jailer took Paul and Silas to his own home

00:02:40.970 --> 00:02:45.160
There he fed them and listened as they told him about Jesus.

00:02:45.160 --> 00:02:49.070
“Men,” he said, “what must I do to be saved?”

00:02:49.070 --> 00:02:51.070
Paul and Silas smiled.

00:02:51.070 --> 00:02:53.560
“Just believe!” they said.

00:02:53.560 --> 00:02:57.160
“Believe in the Lord Jesus, and you will be saved.”

00:02:57.160 --> 00:03:02.830
Before the night was over, Paul and Silas baptized the jailer and all his family.

00:03:02.830 --> 00:03:06.990
Paul and Silas praised God when bad things happened to them.

00:03:06.990 --> 00:03:10.220
They showed the jailer about Jesus’ love.

00:03:10.220 --> 00:03:14.450
You can share about Jesus too, by doing what is right!

